Explanation:

We iterate through the array nums and update the gcd variable. When we find a number that divides the current gcd, we update gcd to the smaller of the two numbers. After iterating through the entire array, we increment the count variable and return the final count. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because we iterate through the array once, and a space complexity of O(1) as we only use a constant amount of space for the gcd and count variables.

